# No Translucent Components

Avoid translucent components in the dashboard and UI. Use **solid colors** instead of opacity-based backgrounds and borders.

## Avoid

- `bg-brand-green/5`, `bg-brand-green/10`, `bg-brand-green/20` (translucent backgrounds)
- `border-brand-green/20`, `border-border/50` (translucent borders)
- `bg-surface-hover/50` for cards and content areas

## Prefer

- **Backgrounds**: `bg-brand-green-dark`, `bg-brand-green`, `bg-surface` (solid)
- **Borders**: `border-brand-green`, `border-brand-green-dark`, `border-border` (solid)
- **Active/highlight states**: `bg-brand-green-dark` instead of `bg-brand-green/20`

## Examples

```tsx
// ❌ Translucent card
<Card className="bg-brand-green/5 border-brand-green/20">

// ✅ Solid card (use app's brand green)
<Card className="bg-brand-green-dark border-brand-green">
```

```tsx
// ❌ Translucent icon circle
<div className="rounded-full bg-brand-green/20">

// ✅ Solid icon circle (use app's brand green)
<div className="rounded-full bg-brand-green-dark">
```

## Text/icon contrast on green

When using `bg-brand-green-dark` or `bg-brand-green`, ensure text and icons are high contrast:
- **bg-brand-green-dark** (dark green) → use `text-white` for text and icons
- **bg-brand-green** (bright green) → use `text-black` for text and icons

## Exceptions

Translucency is acceptable for:
- Modal/overlay backdrops (`bg-black/50`, `bg-black/80`)
- Hero gradients and decorative blur effects
- Hover states on interactive elements (e.g. `hover:bg-brand-green/50`)
